{"word":"ἐπόμνυμι","slug":"ἐπόμνυμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπόμνυμι</b></el> <el>(and <el>-ύω</el>) (<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-ομοῦμαι</el>) (aor1 <el>-ώμοσα</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to swear after, swear accordingly</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>: <i>to take an oath besides</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, <i>to swear by</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <a href='S:apud (quoted in)'>ap.</a> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to swear to</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to swear that</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>5. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> in aor1 <a href='S:participle'>part.</a>, <el>ἐπομόσας</el> <i>upon oath</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}